pageContext.claim: “We've had flu years where we lost 100,000 people. The flu is a very serious problem for this country also. And we've been losing them -- Scott, what kind of a number have we lost over the years with flus? Into the hundreds of thousands?”
pageContext.analysis: More than 100,000 people have died from the season flu in the past, but not recently. For the last decade, the seasonal flu has resulted in 12,000 to 61,000 deaths, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.
